WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.360 --> 00:00:13.360
Detective Chief Inspector Nicola Crooks
 was released from custody today

2
00:00:13.600 --> 00:00:18.160
after the Metropolitan Police Cyber Crime
Unit eventually uncovered evidence

3
00:00:18.400 --> 00:00:22.600
that the incriminating social media posts
 were part of an organised attempt

4
00:00:22.800 --> 00:00:25.160
to discredit the case against APT.

5
00:00:25.600 --> 00:00:28.280
Although the cyber detectives
 were thorough in their evidence,

6
00:00:28.440 --> 00:00:30.720
there was a delay
 in getting it to the court.

7
00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:34.520
The judge presiding, Justice Nowater,
was unhappy with lateness

8
00:00:34.520 --> 00:00:37.640
of the evidence,
 putting the prosecution on the back foot.

9
00:00:38.040 --> 00:00:42.720
However, APT eventually pled guilty,
 but only after much deliberation.

10
00:00:42.880 --> 00:00:45.880
For more on this,
 we go to our crime reporter, Will Tellit.

